OL,3,CJersey will vote on final assisted
OL,4,Cdying law in December
OL,6,FSafeguards have been a key part of
OL,7,Fdiscussions about assisted dying
OL,8,Flegislation across the British Isles,
OL,9,Fdue to concerns that vulnerable people
OL,10,Fcould be coerced to end their lives.
OL,12,FTo combat this, the UK and the Isle of
OL,13,FMan will bring in a specific
OL,14,F'coercion' offence punishable by up to
OL,15,F14 years in prison.
OL,17,FJersey has not yet defined this but
OL,18,FITV News understands coercion would
OL,19,Flikely fall under the island's
OL,20,Fexisting homicide law, rather than
OL,21,Fbeing dealt with separately.
